/tmp
# R6-OPT-A6: per-run raw provenance dumps from scripts/paired-ab-runner.mjs --
# generated output, accumulates one timestamped JSON per invocation, not source.
/docs/perf/paired_ab_runs/
# R13-10 (task #280): scratch raw command-output logs from bench/test/iai
# sweeps (`docs/perf/_raw_*.log`) are throwaway by default -- ignored so ad-hoc
# local runs never accumulate as untracked noise (22 such files had piled up
# across R9-R11 before this rule). EXCEPTION: when a perf-gate report in
# docs/perf/*.md cites specific `_raw_*.log` filenames as its evidence (the
# R13-6/R13-8/R13-9 gate docs already do this), `git add -f` those specific
# files so the cited evidence is reproducible from the commit, not just from
# a re-run. Do not `git add -f` logs a doc does not name.
/docs/perf/_raw_*.log
